<h1>Directory of Religious Tolerance Resources</h1>

    <p>
        <a href="/">Home</a> >
            <a href="/Society">Society</a>  >             <a href="/Society/Religion_and_Spirituality">Religion and Spirituality</a>  >             <a href="/Society/Religion_and_Spirituality/Religious_Tolerance">Religious Tolerance</a>         </p>

<p><p>Religious, adjective, having a strong belief in a god or gods, or any such system of belief and worship. Tolerance, noun, willingness to accept behavior and beliefs which are different from your own, although you might not agree with or approve of them. It is very easy to see, from the definitions alone, why Religious Tolerance can be a difficult subject. Strong beliefs often make tolerance difficult at best. The sites listed here in Religious Tolerance are intended to provide information and understanding of differing beliefs in order to increase acceptance.</p></p>

<h2>Subcategories</h2>
<ul id="triple">
    <li><a href="/Society/Religion_and_Spirituality/Religious_Tolerance/Articles" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Articles</strong></a></li>
    <li><a href="/Society/Religion_and_Spirituality/Scientology/Church_of_Scientology/Response_to_Critics" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Intolerance of Scientology</strong></a></li>
    <li><a href="/Society/Issues/Race-Ethnic-Religious_Relations" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Race, Ethnic, and Religious Relations</strong></a></li>
</ul>
<div style="clear:both"></div>

<h2>Resources in This Category</h2>
<ul>

    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.center2000.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Center For Reduction of Religious-Based Conflict</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.center2000.org/</strong></font> <br /> Works to reduce religious-based conflict by publicizing its costs to the world, its causes, and by offering long-term solutions.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://earthrenewal.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>EarthRenewal.Org</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://earthrenewal.org/</strong></font> <br /> Social activists&#039; web portal, with over 1,000 external links, discussion form, and pages devoted to areas from Art to World History, all relating to religious tolerance and the beginnings of religious belief.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.forum18.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Forum 18 News Service</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.forum18.org/</strong></font> <br /> Christian initiative to report on threats and actions against the religious freedom of all people, regardless of their religious affiliation.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.international-satsang.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>I.S.A. - International Satsang Association</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.international-satsang.org/</strong></font> <br /> Promoting open access to spiritual resources. The Satsang aims to be &quot;Open Space&quot; where all traditions and authentic ways of spiritual practice are respected.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://iarf.net/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>International Association for Religious Freedom</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://iarf.net/</strong></font> <br /> Describes organization and provides compiled data detailing worldwide religious freedom.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.oneworldinsight.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>One World Insight</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.oneworldinsight.com/</strong></font> <br /> Non-profit group promoting religious tolerance and commonalities through compassion and education.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.religioustolerance.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Ontario Consultants on Religious Tolerance</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.religioustolerance.org/</strong></font> <br /> Having three main purposes: to disseminate accurate religious information, to expose religious fraud, hatred and misinformation, and to disseminate information on &quot;hot&quot; religious topics.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://peaceseeds.elysiumgates.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Peaceseeds</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://peaceseeds.elysiumgates.com/</strong></font> <br /> Comparison of the sacred texts of various religions on a variety of subjects. Focusing on the commonality between all traditions.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.mcgill.ca/terraferma/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>Terra Ferma</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.mcgill.ca/terraferma/</strong></font> <br /> Project supporting the equitable representation of religion in the media and academia. Includes examples of misrepresentation, statement of purpose and links to related resources.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.corrymeela.org/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Corrymeela Community</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.corrymeela.org/</strong></font> <br /> Almost 30 years of reconciliation work between Catholics and Protestants in Northern Ireland. Includes timelines, recent information, articles and links to more information.</p>
    </li>	
    <li class="listings">
    <h4><a href="http://www.joyofsects.com/" target="_blank" style="text-decoration:none"><strong>The Joy of Sects</strong></a></h4>
	<p><font color="#013C7F"><strong>http://www.joyofsects.com/</strong></font> <br /> Devoted to showing the commonality among the world&#039;s religious traditions.</p>
    </li>	
</ul>

